Title: Words of Radiance (The Stormlight Archive, #2)
Author: Brandon Sanderson
My Review: This book. THIS BOOOOK! This is quite honestly one of my favourite books of all time. I absolutely loved following Shallan‚Äôs history and growth. It was sad and dark and beautiful all the same. Even her dry humour and quick tongue became all the more lovable and comforting. In the same vein, I really appreciated the internal moral struggle that Kaladin went through. Such a brilliant book with such radiant characters. We all just need a bit of insanity to get through our own storms.

Title: The Way of Kings (The Stormlight Archive, #1)
Author: Brandon Sanderson
My Review: I quite liked this book for many reasons. I almost put it on par with Pillars of the Earth in terms of the sheer detail in the exploration of each character and their inner worlds, thoughts and emotions. Firstly, I like it for its size - I am a sucker for long stories. I remember when I was reaching the end of the book I felt as though all the revelations seemed a but rushed because I like a long stew. Secondly, I like it for rekindling my love for fantasy and world building again. Sanderson does an absolutely incredible job at describing parts of Roshar and the jambalaya of cultures of its inhabitants. Yes, there were some faults - some redundant descriptions and very bad puns from Shallan, and at times simplistic prose (when one of the things I love about reading are how authors play around with language) - but I still loved it despite those.
